{{DISPLAYTITLE:Level 456: "Laundry Rooftop"}}
<div class="onlydark">{{Notice|body=Light mode is recommended.}}</div>
{{Class Custom Image|color=#75623e|security=Partially Unstable|entity=Minimal Entity Count|safety=Safe|bg-image=Bricks.jpg}}
'''Level 456''' is the 457th level of the Backrooms. 
==Description==
'''Level 456''' resembles a vast area with rows of drying laundry. The floor is composed of red bricks laid out in different patterns throughout the level. There is no day and night cycle – it is always daytime. The weather is permanently sunny, but rarely sparse clouds can be observed. The temperature is consistently 25°C (77°F), with a light breeze sometimes carrying through the level.
{{Blurimage|file=Laundry Forest 004.jpg|hovertext=Long linen sheets|caption=The first image of '''Level 456''', showing the classic long linen sheets.}}

The type of laundry is the same in each square section of 50x50 m (164 ft). Often the laundry contains white linen sheets, reaching down to the floor, largely obstructing further view of the level. Other colors and sections with clothes, such as trousers or shirts, have been sighted. The dryness of the laundry varies as well, ranging from dry to completely drenched. However, the most common sections are made out of slightly moist linen sheets. The liquid responsible for the moisture has been proven to be [[Object 1|Almond Water]] and is safe to drink. Other consumable items have not been found at this level.

The laundry is always hung up slightly over the height of the tallest person around. In a test where one scientist climbed on the shoulders of another, the upward growth of the level was visible to the naked eye, proving that the level adjusts itself to visitors. This property of the level has been deemed to be the most effective way to identify the approach of other people or entities in '''Level 456'''. Similar tests have been tried with cameras. Surprisingly, objects do not have the same influence on the level, as an invisible ceiling stops objects from reaching above the clothesline.

Scientists have proposed the theory that '''Level 456''' differentiates things on the level into two groups. These are classified into 'visitors' and 'objects'. Visitors are humans, animals as well as entities. Many argue that all living beings are seen as visitors but more tests with plants and bacteria have to be conducted to come to a definitive conclusion on this. The level adjusts itself around visitors. The level will ensure that visitors do not see over the clothesline and objects do not disappear while under visitor supervision. Everything that is not a visitor is categorized as an object. The level does not adjust to objects. There are two subgroups of objects; objects that belong to the level and possess a designated spot and objects that do not belong to the level. If these objects are not observed by a visitor the level will try to restore the objects to their designated place and state. For objects belonging to the level, this means being set to its original place and state, while it will try to eject objects that do not originally belong to the level.
{{Blurimage|align=left|file=no-clipping house.png|hovertext=House partially no-clipped |caption=This is a sketch of a partially no-clipped house, found on the level.}}
<br>Another feature of '''Level 456''' is the laundry's ability to intercept the transmission of sound, scent, heat as well as radiation. All of these properties are largely swallowed by the surrounding laundry. This makes for an easier escape from dangerous entities but also heightens the difficulty of noticing when other people or entities are approaching.

In some instances, buildings from other levels can partially no-clip into '''Level 456'''. As these are viewed as objects by the level, they do not exceed or expand the ceiling of the level. These buildings are internally still connected with the original level.  
<div class="pagefooter"></div>
While '''Level 456''' is generally safe, the following instructions should be followed while in the level:
* When staying for longer than an hour seek out shadows periodically to escape the sun. The laundry can be used to make temporary shelters.
*If a base is established it is always necessary for someone to stay there at all times to ensure that the base will not disappear.
*When staying for multiple days it is important to bring food with you, as the only edible thing on this level is [[Object 1|Almond Water]].
*Should an entity be encountered on this level, it is advised not to interact with it and to hide between the laundry.

=='''The Edge'''==
{{Blurimage|file=Lübeck 2.jpg|hovertext=View over a city|caption=Picture taken at The Edge from a person who grew up in Lübeck, Germany.}}
After walking through '''Level 456''' some wanderers encountered the area known as '''The Edge'''. This area is the reason for the level's nickname the '''Laundry Rooftop''', as it looks like the edge of a rooftop. Unlike the rest of the level, this area is a finite, Euclidean space, of exactly 50 to 50 m – the same as the sections of laundry found in the level. 

When looking down one can see what seems to be a bustling city life, although details can not be made out, as everything is slightly blurry. The cityscape emulates cities very familiar to the wanderer, although a lot of the buildings are built with the same red bricks as the floor in '''Level 456'''. The edge of the rooftop is lined with a small wall of about 40 cm (15.7 in). While it seems easy to jump off the edge, this is not possible, as the same invisible wall is found around the edge as the one that can be observed at the ceiling of the level.

Just as buildings or other inanimate objects can disappear in '''Level 456''', the same is true for '''The Edge'''. If one encounters '''The Edge''' but turns away from it, chances are high that it will not be found again anytime soon. 

==Entities==
Entities are found exceedingly rarely on '''Level 456'''. In most instances in which entities were encountered on this level, the entity was transported to this level together with the wanderer documenting the case. The survival rate of these instances is very high, as the newly arrived entities take from around 10 minutes up to an hour to adjust to the level. During this time, they are engaging in atypical behavior such as staying completely still or walking in random directions. This time can be used to make a successful escape from the entity. It is suspected that no entities spawn naturally on this level, but this cannot be confirmed.

== Entrances and Exits==
=== Entrances===
*The safest way to reach '''Level 456''' is to climb on a rooftop at any level where this is possible, having a small chance to lead to this level. An example of this is [[Level 385]].
*'''Level 456''' can also be accessed through all levels containing buildings, as it is possible for parts of buildings to be transported into this level. This way of accessing this level is discouraged, as these connections are inherently unstable. 
===Exits===  
* Just as '''Level 456''' can be entered through buildings that are partially transported to this level, the level can also be exited through these. This way of exiting is discouraged, for the same reason as entering this way is.
*The second known way to exit this level is to find a trapdoor, leading to a level where rooftop access is possible, such as [[Level 385]].

